description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to develop your skills in the specialist area of gastroenterology? We are looking for an extra person to join our team to help provide a specialist clinical service to the gastroenterology MDT, wards and outpatient clinics. The Oxford University Hospitals Trust has a well-established gastroenterology service, led by very supportive Gastro Consultants, whom you will work closely with. You will be responsible for covering the gastro medical ward and gastro outpatient clinics (including general gastro and IBS). As a tertiary referral centre we provide a service for the full range of gastro conditions. We are looking for someone to focus on luminal and acute inpatient eating disorders whilst working closely with two other dietitians who will focus on liver and coeliac, sharing IBS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by the experienced team lead dietitian and cover for each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a commitment to personal development and CPD and an expectation that all staff are involved in corporate departmental project work and teaching of other healthcare professionals. All staff are actively involved in student training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 8th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proposed Interview date: Wednesday 18th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please take a moment to read our recruitment pack for more information about the role, the team and the Trust. For more information about this exciting opportunity, please contact Catherine Nash, Gastroenterology Team Lead Dietitian on Catherine.nash@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
